snippet.textDisplay:
Okay, what is the point of using Robert B Parker’s books if all you’re going to keep is the names and the city?

Spenser is a witty, literate, old-school private eye who is a gourmet cook in his spare time. Hawk is a cool and deadly enforcer with a taste for pricey champagne and designer clothing.

This? This is a generic action movie. And I actually love action movies, but I’m already annoyed by this one.

snippet.textDisplay:
They took every unique element of the characters and wiped them. Hawk is no longer the smoldering, Beacon Hill-dwelling force of nature. Hard to be respectable muscle if you live in the back of a gym. I'll bet Spenser has lost his culinary and literary interests as well. He's obviously given up on his moral code if he's in prison. Susan goes from sultry, Jewish PhD. to peroxide bimbo? Not much Robert Parker left here, folks.


So what sets this apart now? We're left with another cookie cutter detective movie. Yeah, I'll watch it. Then I'll bitch about it some more.
